# Task: Vectorized 2D Map Fit Engine

## Planning
- [x] Understand root cause: lmfit holds GIL + Windows IPC overhead > per-task compute time
- [x] Confirm threading doesn't help (GIL locked)
- [x] Confirm batch multiprocessing kills parallelism 
- [/] Design new vectorized engine architecture

## Implementation

### Core engine (`spectroview/model/map_fit_engine.py`)
- [ ] `MapFitEngine` class with numpy model functions
- [ ] Vectorized peak models: Lorentzian, Gaussian, PseudoVoigt, Fano
- [ ] scipy.optimize.least_squares direct call (bypasses lmfit Python overhead)
- [ ] Row-major scan order (neighbor propagation logic)
- [ ] Result storage as numpy matrix `params_matrix[n_spectra, n_params]`
- [ ] Compatibility layer: `build_fitspy_result(idx)` → MSpectrum with result_fit

### Thread integration ([spectroview/viewmodel/utils.py](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/utils.py))
- [ ] `VectorizedMapFitThread` QThread class (replaces [ApplyFitModelThread](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/utils.py#128-341) for maps)
- [ ] Emits real-time progress as spectra are fitted
- [ ] Stores `MapFitEngine` result accessible to ViewModel

### ViewModel integration ([spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_maps.py](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_maps.py))
- [ ] Detect when vectorized engine is applicable (2D map, supported models)
- [ ] Route map fits through `VectorizedMapFitThread`
- [ ] Retrieve per-pixel results from `MapFitEngine.params_matrix`
- [ ] Fall back to existing [ApplyFitModelThread](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/utils.py#128-341) for unsupported cases

### Vertical compatibility
- [ ] After vectorized fit, populate spectrum.result_fit on-demand when user selects a pixel
- [ ] Ensure [collect_fit_results()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_spectra.py#1096-1240) still works with the new engine

## Verification
